<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Aggression level dete=
rmines
how aggressive computer players are.</span><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-=
ansi-language:
EN-NZ;mso-no-proof:yes'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Research Costs determ=
ine how
fast research occurs in the galaxy, and thus how quickly new components bec=
ome
available for use in ships and bases. You can use the slider to set common
values for research costs, or you can type in your own custom value in the =
box
at the right.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Finally, you can also=
 specify
how many space creatures and pirates are present in the galaxy. For pirates=
 you
can also control how far away they start from empires. You can also specify
that Destroyed Pirates do not restart, allowing you to more easliy clear pi=
rate
presence from a section of the galaxy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Click the Next button=
 at
bottom right to continue to step 3 (Colonization and Territory).<o:p></o:p>=
</span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Step 3: Colonization and Territory<o:p=
></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_32" o:=
spid=3D"_x0000_s1031"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:228.85pt;margi=
n-top:0;
 width:280.05pt;height:232.65pt;z-index:251658752;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:page;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image006.jpg" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D373 height=3D310
src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image007.jpg" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_32"><![endif]><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Colony Prevalence influences the number of colon=
izable
planets and moons in the galaxy. Higher prevalences means denser empires wi=
th
colonies packed closer together.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Independent Alien Life
determines how many independent populations of aliens exist in the galaxy a=
nd
how large they are.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Colony Influence Range controls how far your empire&#8=
217;s
territorial influence projects out from your colonies.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>You may also choose to enforce limits on how far new
colonies can be established from any empire&#8217;s existing colonies. If t=
his
is turned on, then you cannot establish new colonies further than the indic=
ated
range from any of your existing colonies. However you may still take over o=
ther
empire&#8217;s colonies outside this range.</p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal>Click the Next button at bottom right to continue to s=
tep 4
(<span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Your Race</span>).</p>

<h3><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_18" o:spid=3D"_x0000_s1=
030"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:228.65pt;margi=
n-top:0;
 width:279.85pt;height:232.1pt;z-index:251657728;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image004.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D373 height=3D309
src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image008.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_18"><![endif]><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Step 4: Your Race<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In step 4 (Your Race)=
 you
select which alien race you will play as. Choose a race from the drop-down =
list
at top-left.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Each alien race has u=
nique
characteristics that alter their style of play. This includes a set of
resources that provide special bonuses for the race, as well as race-specif=
ic
victory conditions.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Click the Next button=
 at
bottom right to continue to step 5 (Your Empire)</span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Step 5: Your Empire<o:p></o:p></span><=
/h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In the Your Empire st=
ep you
can set all the characteristics of your empire, including its name, colors =
and
flag.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_7" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1029"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:226.7pt;margin=
-top:0;
 width:277.9pt;height:231.05pt;z-index:251660800;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:page;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image009.jpg" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D371 height=3D308
src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image010.jpg" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_7"><![endif]><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;</span>Fr=
om here
you can also set your empire&#8217;s size, it&#8217;s technology level and
it&#8217;s starting location in the galaxy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Home System determine=
s the
favorability of your starting system. In more favorable systems your starti=
ng
colony will have higher quality and size. There will also be additional
colonizable planets beyond your starting colony.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Corruption determines=
 the
level of corruption and income loss across your empire. This setting only
affects your empire, not other empires in the galaxy. All other empires use
&#8220;Normal&#8221; corruption setting. Thus you can use this setting to m=
ake
either an easier, or more difficult game for yourself against the computer
players.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>At the bottom of this=
 screen
you can select the government style you want to play as. Details on the
selected governments are shown here to help you decide which government you
want to play.</span><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_9" o:sp=
id=3D"_x0000_s1028"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:229.85pt;margi=
n-top:0;
 width:281.05pt;height:233.75pt;z-index:251655680;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:page;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image017.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D375 height=3D312
src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image011.png" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_9"><![endif]><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Pirate Factions<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>If you selected to pl=
ay as a
pirate in step 1 (Playstyle) then there are different options on the Your
Empire </span><span lang=3DEN-NZ style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-NZ'>screen</=
span><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You must select a pir=
ate
playstyle for your pirate faction from the dropdown list. Each particular
Pirate Playstyle provides various bonuses and penalties that focus your pir=
ate
faction towards different activities. Pirate Playstyles also determine what=
 victory
conditions your pirate faction will pursue.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Each pirate playstyle=
 is
explained in detail when you select it.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Click the Next button=
 at
bottom right to continue to step 6 (Other Empires)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Step 6: Other Empires<o:p></o:p></span=
></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In the Other Empires =
step you
can determine the settings for all the other empires in the galaxy.<o:p></o=
:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_28" o:=
spid=3D"_x0000_s1027"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:229.4pt;margin=
-top:0;
 width:280.6pt;height:233.2pt;z-index:251661824;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:page;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image024.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D374 height=3D311
src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image012.jpg" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_28"><![endif]><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>If you wish you can automatically generate all o=
ther
empires at random, specifying how many empires to generate.<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Or you can specify the
details of each empire individually in the grid in the middle of the screen.
Here you can set up specific competitor empires, including their race,
government type, size, technology level and how close they start to your em=
pire
in the galaxy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Finally, you can deci=
de
whether new empires should spontaneously appear during the game. If you che=
ck
this option, independent colonies can start new empires when they reach a
sufficient size and development level.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Click the Next button=
 to
continue to step 7 (Victory Conditions)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Step 7: Victory Conditions<o:p></o:p><=
/span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_10" o:=
spid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:230.15pt;margi=
n-top:.45pt;
 width:281.35pt;height:233.25pt;z-index:251656704;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:page;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image011.png" o:title=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square" anchorx=3D"page"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D375 height=3D311
src=3D"Screen_StartNewGame_files/image014.jpg" align=3Dright hspace=3D12 v:=
shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_10"><![endif]><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In the Victory Conditions step you can choose ho=
w to
win the game.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Valid victory conditi=
ons
include any combination of the following:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l=
1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol;mso-no-proof:yes'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><sp=
an
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Territory</span></b><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:=
yes'>:
control the specified percentage of all colonies in the galaxy<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:=
l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol;mso-no-proof:yes'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><sp=
an
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Population</span></b><span style=3D'mso-no-proof=
:yes'>:
control the specified percentage of the galaxy&#8217;s total population<o:p=
></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:=
l1 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol;mso-no-proof:yes'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><sp=
an
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Economy</span></b><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:ye=
s'>:
your empire&#8217;s private economy generates the specified percentage of t=
he
galaxy&#8217;s total economic output<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1=
 level1 lfo4'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol;mso-no-proof:yes'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><sp=
an
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Race-specific conditons</span></b><span
style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>: each empire must reach it&#8217;s own unique
race-specific victory conditions<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>The value for Victory
Threshold Percent determines the proportion of the above victory conditions
that must be met for victory.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You can also choose t=
o have
victory conditions only apply after the game has progressed for the specifi=
ed
number of years. This setting can prevent a game from finishing prematurely,
when empire progress may fluctuate more noticeably at the start of the game=
.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You may also set a ti=
me
limit, where the game finishes after the specified number of years. At this
point the winner is determined by the empire with the highest total strateg=
ic
value of all its colonies.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>At the left you can c=
hoose to
disable story events from the original Distant Worlds storyline by unchecki=
ng
the checkbox. This will turn off all backstory events, including debris fie=
lds,
restricted zones and planet destroyer construction projects.<o:p></o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Below this you can al=
so
choose to disable the Return Of The Shakturi story events and victory
conditions by unchecking the checkbox.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Special events new in=
 Distant
Worlds Legends can be enabled or disabled with the checkbox &#8220;Enable
Disasters and other events&#8221;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Under this you can ch=
oose
whether to enable race-specific events in the game.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Finally you can enabl=
e or
disable story events related to the Age of Shadows.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Note that some settin=
gs in
the Victory Conditions screen may be disabled and unavailable depending on =
the
game playstyle chosen in step 1.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Once all of the setti=
ngs are
complete, click the &#8220;Start the Game&#8221; button to generate the gal=
axy
and begin playing!<o:p></o:p></span></p>

